<DESCRIPT>  CHARITY  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  IF YOU want to have a good time for a good cause, here's a list of upcoming
social events benefiting Bay Area charities.;    (box) Camp Fire Council of
Santa Clara and Santa Cruz Counties benefits from a performance of Steve
Silver's "Beach Blanket Babylon" at 8 p.m. Wednesday at Flint Center, DeAnza
Community College, 21250 Stevens Creek Blvd., Cupertino. The show, now in its
17th year in San Francisco, is an entertaining extravaganza of costumes,
singing and dancing. Dress circle ticket holders will attend a pre-show gala
with food, door prizes and an auction from 5:30 to 7:30 p.m. Dress circle
tickets are $80 and available by calling (408) 988-6969. Tickets to the
performance alone are $15, $22 and $27.50 and available through the Flint
Center Box Office, (408) 864-8816.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  'BEACH BLANKET' BENEFITS CAMP FIRE  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Revels With a Cause  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     (box) Junior Achievement of Santa Clara County's 1991 Business Hall of Fame
Dinner and Laureate Induction Ceremony is 6:30 p.m. Wednesday at the Fairmont
Hotel, 170 S. Market St., San Jose. Laureates are Sandra Kurtzig, chief
executive officer of ASK Computer Systems and the first woman to win this
award; James Morgan, CEO of Applied Materials; Gordon Moore, chairman of Intel
Corp.; James Treybig, CEO of Tandem Computers; and the late John Crummey,
founder and former chairman of FMC Corp. Tickets for the black-tie evening are
$200 for the laureate reception and dinner and $150 for the general reception
and dinner. Information and reservations: (408) 943-1930.;    (box) Menlo
School's 41st annual fund-raiser, "Cirque de Menlo," includes a noon luncheon
and a 6 p.m. dinner dance Friday in the Haynes-Prim Pavilion, Menlo School, 50
Valparaiso Ave., Atherton. A show of spring fashions from Macy's will take
place at both events. The black-tie optional evening also includes an auction.
Luncheon tickets are $55 and dinner-dance tickets are $135. Information and
reservations: (415) 324-0629.;    (box) The Italian American Heritage
Foundation hosts its second annual Opera San Jose Benefit Dinner at 6 p.m.
Friday at the I.A.H.F. Cultural Center, 425 N. 4th St., San Jose. Tickets are
$20. Information and reservations: (408) 293-7122.  </TEXT>
